Client Interests

A client can be interested in a category.

If a client specifies a property name that is already in a category of interest,

the property name is essentially ignored, and they recieve all the messages from the category

If the client were to remove that category from their interests, the property would still be ignored.

If a client specifies a property name that is not within their categories of interest

That category is placed in the "category all" but not the "categorywhole" container

If they attempt to remove the category to which their specified property belongs,
they will recieve the specified property still.

Property names are deemed a completely separate concern compared to categories of interest UNLESS

the specified property name belongs to a category to which the client has interest. At which point
the property name is ignored. And only the category is used then on out.

The mechanism for properties is used by checking a clients